               <msContents>
                  <summary>Draft of a petition from Panopolis (modern name: Akhmim), Egypt, written on papyrus. Written by Ammon, the well-known scholastikos, or lawyer. Mentions Alexandria. Papyrus belongs to the archive of Ammon. Recto has a draft of a petition in Greek (P.Duk.inv. 229 R)</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 7.6 x 4.0 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">4 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the verso in Ammon's informal hand; written across the fibers on the recto in Ammon's informal hand</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 229 V was formerly P.Duk.inv. G 229 V</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
